    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of the 996.2 generation, featuring the coveted wide-body aesthetic and integrated Turbo-spec suspension geometry. Power is delivered via the 3.6L M96 flat-six, featuring VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve across the rev range. This example boasts a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The all-wheel-drive system utilizes a viscous mapping for superior lateral grip, complemented by four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers and cross-drilled rotors. Meticulously maintained with an unblemished DME report and zero evidence of bore scoring, this chassis remains in concours-ready condition, offering a visceral, analog driving experience with total mechanical peace of mind.",
